revision.text:
{{Orphan|date=October 2013}}
'''Atomic Reach''' is a [[real-time computing|real-time]] [[Content management system|content]] optimization engine that analyzes and measures content based on its quality and potential for amplified reach. It also promotes the discovery and sharing of relevant content for a [[writer]], [[publisher]], or [[blogger]]'s target audience.<ref name="betakit">Lindzon, Jared. [http://www.betakit.com/atomic-reach/ "Atomic Reach unveils algorithm that can predict content's success before it's published online"], ''Betakit'', Toronto, 27 August 2013.</ref>
Prior to the launch of the company's content optimization engine, Atomic Reach developed [[content curation]] [[software]].<ref name="theglobeandmail">Reuber, Becky. [https://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/small-business/starting-out/you-believe-you-have-a-winning-idea-how-to-make-others-think-so-too/article8159313/ "You believe you have a winning idea: How to make others think so, too"], ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'', Toronto, 8 February 2013.</ref>
Atomic Reach has received several rounds of funding from notable [[investor]]s including Genwealth Venture Partners.<ref name="markevans.ca">Evans, Mark. [http://www.markevans.ca/2013/01/29/snapshot-of-a-vc-deal-atomic-reach/ "Snapshot of a VC Deal: Atomic Reach"], ''MarkEvans.ca'', Toronto, 29 January 2013.</ref>
