{{Orphan|date=February 2013}}

The '''''MAOL table book''''' ([[Finnish language|Finnish]]: ''MAOL-taulukot'') is a book published by MAOL, the [[Finland|Finnish]] association for teachers of mathematical subjects and distributed by [[Otava (publisher)|Otava]]. It is a book of numeric tables to aid in studying [[mathematics]], [[chemistry]] and [[physics]] at the [[gymnasium (school)|gymnasium]] level. The book includes a list of mathematical notation and symbols, a diverse collection of formulae, and several numeric tables. The Finnish matricular examination board has accepted the book and allowed it to be used in the Finnish [[abitur]] examinations.

The colour of the cover of the book is changed with each edition of the book.

==Literature==
