{{Italic title}}
'''''The Cambridge Guide to English Usage''''' by [[Pam Peters]] is a [[usage dictionary]], giving an up-to-date account of the debatable issues of English usage and written style. It is based on extensive, up-to-date [[corpus linguistics|corpus data]] rather than on the author's personal intuition or prejudice, and differentiates among US, UK, Canadian and Australian usages. British [[lexicographer]] [[Sidney Landau]] remarked:

{{quote|The Cambridge Guide to English Usage is unique in the extent of its coverage of all the major varieties of English and in the degree to which it is based on corpus evidence, that is, on the analysis of vast collections of actual written and spoken language in each of the varieties under study.}}

== See also ==
* ''[[A Dictionary of Modern English Usage]]'' by Fowler
