{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}} {{Use British English|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox pier | name = Tower Millennium Pier | image = File:Tower Millennium Pier from The Tower Bridge Experience (2) - geograph.org.uk - 1271350.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | locale = [[River Thames]], [[London]], UK | type = River bus and tourist/leisure services | design = | construction = | owner = [[London River Services]] | operator = [[London River Services]] | open = | closed = | coordinates = }} '''Tower Millennium Pier''' is a [[pier]] on the [[River Thames]], in [[London]], [[United Kingdom|UK]]. It is operated by [[London River Services]] and served by various river transport and cruise operators. The pier is close to [[Tower Bridge]] and is situated immediately adjacent to the southwest corner of the [[Tower of London]].
==Services== The pier is used by the river bus route RB1 from [[Embankment Pier|Embankment]] to [[Woolwich Arsenal Pier|Woolwich]] (operated by [[MBNA Thames Clippers]]) and [[Westminster Millennium Pier|Westminster]]-[[Greenwich Pier|Greenwich]] tourist boats (operated by City Cruises).<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.tfl.gov.uk/gettingaround/1131.aspx |title = London River Services timetables |author=Transport for London |accessdate =2008-03-30 }}</ref> Private-charter entertainment boats also use Tower Pier.<ref>For example {{cite web |url = http://www.thamesleisure.co.uk/the-definitive-guide-to-london-piers-part-one-tower-millennium-pier/ |title = Thames Leisure |accessdate =2016-08-24 }}</ref>
==History== [[File:City of London skyline from London City Hall - Oct 2008.jpg|thumb|Tower Millennium Pier, with the [[City of London]]'s financial core behind, as seen from [[City Hall (London)|City Hall]]]] Tower Millennium Pier was opened on 14 July by London Mayor [[Ken Livingstone]]. Its creation was funded by the [[Millennium Commission]] as part of the Thames 2000 project, and was one of five new piers provided by the Commission on the Thames (the others being [[Blackfriars Millennium Pier]], [[London Eye Pier]], [[Westminster Millennium Pier]] and [[Millbank Millennium Pier]]). The pier has at its upstream end a small cruise terminal facility which is used for processing passengers and baggage transferred by boat from cruise ships berthed alongside HMS Belfast. The Tower Pier project was part of an integrated transport and regeneration strategy for the Thames led by London's [[Cross River Partnership]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.millennium.gov.uk/cgi-bin/item.cgi?id=1213 |title = Ken Livingstone Opens New Millennium Commission Funded Pier |accessdate = 2008-03-30 |date = 2000-07-13 |work = The Millennium Commission press release |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20081209000734/http://www.millennium.gov.uk/cgi-bin/item.cgi?id=1213 |archivedate = 9 December 2008 |df = dmy-all }} </ref>
==Connections== *[[Tower Hill tube station|Tower Hill Underground station]] and [[Tower Gateway DLR station]], [[Fenchurch Street railway station]] {{rail-interchange|london|underground}} {{rail-interchange|london|dlr}} {{rail-interchange|london|rail}} * [[St. Katharine Pier]] on the other side of [[Tower Bridge]] for [[Crown River Cruises]]. *[[London Buses]] [[London Buses route 15|15]]; [[London Buses route 15H|15H]]; [[London Buses route N15|N15]]; RV1
==Lifeboat pier move== In 2002 the [[Royal National Lifeboat Institution|RNLI]]'s Thames [[Lifeboat (rescue)|lifeboat]] service was introduced to the River Thames following the [[Marchioness disaster]], and Tower Pier was initially used as a base for the lifeboat service. In 2006 the RNLI station moved up-river to a new base, the former Waterloo Police Pier on [[Victoria Embankment]] next to [[Waterloo Bridge]], which took the name Tower Lifeboat Station.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.natoli.co.uk/rnli/station.htm |title = Tower Lifeboat Station website |accessdate =2007-11-13 |author = |date = 2006-05-08 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080123105559/http://www.natoli.co.uk/rnli/station.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2008-01-23}} </ref>
